  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Staff Nurse",
  "description": "<p><u><strong>Work location: HongKah North Daycare Centre</strong></u><br /></p><p><u><strong>Job purpose</strong></u><br /></p><p>To provide optimal level of care in accordance to established policies and procedures.</p><p>To assist in activities and programs promoting healthy aging for clients.</p><p>Supervise Nursing Team comprising of Enrolled Nurse, Nursing Aides and Healthcare Assistant to ensure optimal delivery of required care to the clients.</p><p><u><strong>Key Responsibilites:</strong></u></p><ul><li>Deliver client-centric and compassionate in nursing care according to clients needs and conditions .</li><li>Montior, assess and evaluate clients condition to implement a care plan.</li><li>Perform clinical procedure (e.g. NGT insertion, catheterization etc.) as and when required.</li><li>Observe and assess the health of the clients, monitor vitals and reactions to treatment and medications; look for changes in behavior and condition.</li><li>Follow up the ensure continuity of clients care plan.</li><li>Travel to sites / centres</li></ul><p><u><strong>Qualifications & Skills Required:</strong></u></p><ul><li>Diploma or degree in nursing</li><li>Registered with SNB</li><li>3 years clinical experience in eldercare sector will be advantage</li><li>Dynamic team player with good interpersonal communication and presentation skills</li></ul>",
