    "description": "<p>SASCO Senior Citizens' Home (SSCH) was first set up on 21 January, 1981 at a HDB void deck in Telok Blangah to provide lodging and care for the destitute elderly regardless of race, language or religion. We are affiliated to the National Council of Social Service (NCSS) and is a member of the NCSS Charitable Fund.</p>\n<p>SSCH's current Sheltered Home at Evergreen Place (Hong San) is able to accommodate up to a total of 102 seniors, and we run 4 Senior Care Centres and 2 Senior Activity Centres in various parts of Singapore.</p>",
